snippet.title: Amber Guyger Judge Tammy Kemp Knew Joshua Brown Needed Protection | "I'm Surprised He Came"
snippet.description:
Joshua Brown expressed he was in fear for his life. He was forced into the Amber Guyger trial via subpoena. Lee Merritt spoke on Full Circle Anderson Coopers show on CNN. He stated it’s likely Joshua’s past caught up with him, but nobody should be ruled out including Dallas PD. The courts knew Joshua Brown was in fear for his life. During Joshua’s Testimony there was an intermission for a break. Audio unintentionally was heard of Judge Tammy Kemp “of course he’s here” “I’m surprised he came” They failed to protect this witness, especially having everything broadcasted live via stream. I personally feel this maybe he past catching up with him but everything needs to be looked into. Joshua Brown would have also been a witness testimony for the civil case. 

New York Post:
Brown fled the state for California, where he remained as the trial got underway, according to Meritt.
But prosecutors “hounded him” and threatened to issue a warrant for his arrest if he didn’t appear in court. “So he got on a plane and came straight from the airport to the courthouse,” Merritt said.
Once he arrived, Brown met with the judge in her chambers about his concerns, but ultimately ended up taking the stand, Meritt said 
https://nypost.com/2019/10/08/joshua-brown-fled-texas-to-avoid-testifying-against-in-amber-guyger-case/
